From:Paul Senior
AMJ: "Since the MLP stocks in this ETN is held by JP Morgan". I don't know that
there are any MLP stocks actually held in the ETN. The ETN is ultimately a
note, a promise to pay. Until somebody corrects me, I believe ETN's compared to
ETF's have additional risk: the credit risk of the issuer. I don't know why I
should take that risk or why AMJ would be better than something like TYN, the
current mlp ETF that I hold.
