$308M. If I use CT's debt, $2.1B per Yahoo, and assume that that's all the
further debt that's subject to possible write-off, (i.e no off balance-sheet
obligations), then worst-case as much as 15% roughly of the debt (i.e $315M)
would have to be written off before tbv evaporates. Not that that would
